      • getOperationSchemes

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getOperationSchemes​(ToShapeId service,
                                                            ToShapeId operation)
        Gets the effective authentication schemes of an operation bound to a service in priority order.

        The computed result is based on either the presence of the auth trait applied to the operation, the auth trait applied to the service it's bound to, or the entire list of auth schemes supported by the protocols trait of the service.

        This method will return an empty List in the case of invalid or missing shapes.

        Parameters:
        service - Service that the operation is bound to.
        operation - Operation to check.
        Returns:
        Returns the computed authentication schemes.

      • getOperationSchemes

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getOperationSchemes​(ToShapeId service,
                                                            ToShapeId operation,
                                                            java.lang.String protocolName)
        Gets the effective authentication schemes of an operation bound to a service that are compatible with a specific protocol of the service in priority order.

        The result is ordered by either the effective auth trait of the operation or the list of protocols on the service.

        Parameters:
        service - Service that the operation is bound to.
        operation - Operation to check.
        protocolName - Protocol to limit the result.
        Returns:
        Returns the computed authentication schemes compatible with the protocol.
